National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with civil society leaders to discuss human rights issues ahead of President Obama's trip to Cuba. Rice emphasized the importance of dialogue and President Obama's efforts to normalize relations with Cuba. She reiterated that during the President's visit, he will meet with Cuban independent civil society chosen by the White House. Rice emphasized the United States' commitment to universal values and human rights, including the right to free speech, peaceful assembly, and association. She stated that the United States will continue to support these universal rights in Cuba and elsewhere.